The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Vijay Hazare laid to rest

Vadodara: Vijay Samuel Hazare was laid to rest in the Methodist Church premises in Nizampura area here on Sunday. The legendary cricketer died on Saturday after a prolonged battle with intestinal cancer. 

Former Test players Chandu Borde, D.K. Gaekwad, Kiran More, Aunshuman Gaekwad and several BCCI officials were among those present during the burial. City mayor Naranbhai Patel and district collector Bhagyesh Jha also paid their respects. 

Borde said Don Bradman had high regards for Hazare. 

Borde, who led India in Australia in 1968, said Bradman had enquired about Hazare?s health during his meeting with the Indian team and asked him (Borde) to convey his regards to Hazare. (PTI) 

